    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-23T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-23T20:00:00-05:00" n="772"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/667: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-23T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 23, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Garcesgana Cabinet has resigned. Demonstrations largely by students have
                    continued throughout the day and tonight the streets are filled with milling
                    crowds which are dispersed from time to time by police on foot and horseback.
                    Attack is expected on 2000 students now in possession of University of Chile. I
                    was appealed to by students but declined to take any action and so informed the
                    Foreign Office. It would appear that the old cabinet was unwilling to adopt
                    repressive measures deemed necessary by Ibañez to maintain order. Cable
                    companies received written instructions not to accept any press messages on the
                    situation. Band reports from Antofagasta that attempted mass meeting called this
                    afternoon by local labor unions to express adherence to the students’ labor
                    movement Santiago suppressed by authorities without disorders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
